DIAGNOSIS. — Dorsal surface of gastric region of carapace lacking spine (
Fig. 2
) except in large females. Gastric region slender in appearance, length 0.4 or more of carapace length. Hepatic swellings each topped by tubercle or spine in large females only. Supraocular spines slightly shorter or same length than ocular

Maximum size: ♂ cl 15.3 mm, ♀ cl 19.0 mm (
Dell 1963
).
